#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:10
msgid "Networking"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:12
msgid ""
"**Incremental Istio Deployment**. (Preview) You can now adopt Istio "
"incrementally, more easily than before, by installing only the components"
" you want (e.g, Pilot+Ingress only as the minimal Istio install). Refer "
"to the ``istioctl`` CLI tool for generating a information on customized "
"Istio deployments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:18
msgid ""
"**Automatic Proxy Injection**. We leverage Kubernetes 1.9’s new `mutating"
" webhook feature "
"<https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes/blob/master/CHANGELOG/CHANGELOG-1.9.md"
"#api-machinery>`_ to provide automatic pod-level proxy injection. "
"Automatic injection requires Kubernetes 1.9 or beyond and therefore "
"doesn’t work on older versions. The alpha initializer mechanism is no "
"longer supported. `Learn more </docs/setup/additional-setup/sidecar-"
"injection/#automatic-sidecar-injection>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:27
msgid ""
"**Revised Traffic Rules**. Based on user feedback, we have made "
"significant changes to Istio’s traffic management (routing rules, "
"destination rules, etc.). We would love your continuing feedback while we"
" polish this in the coming weeks."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:33
msgid "Mixer adapters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:35
msgid ""
"**Open Policy Agent**. Mixer now has an authorization adapter "
"implementing the `open policy agent <https://www.openpolicyagent.org>`_ "
"model, providing a flexible fine-grained access control mechanism. `Learn"
" more "
"<https://docs.google.com/document/d/1U2XFmah7tYdmC5lWkk3D43VMAAQ0xkBatKmohf90ICA>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:41
msgid ""
"**Istio RBAC**. Mixer now has a role-based access control adapter. `Learn"
" more </docs/concepts/security/#authorization>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:44
msgid ""
"**Fluentd**. Mixer now has an adapter for log collection through `Fluentd"
" <https://www.fluentd.org>`_. `Learn more "
"</docs/tasks/observability/mixer/logs/fluentd/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:48
msgid ""
"**Stdio**. The stdio adapter now lets you log to files with support for "
"log rotation & backup, along with a host of controls."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:52
msgid "Security"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:54
msgid ""
"**Bring Your Own CA**. There have been many enhancements to the ‘bring "
"your own CA’ feature. `Learn more </docs/tasks/security/citadel-config"
"/plugin-ca-cert/>`_"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:58
msgid "**PKCS8**. Add support for PKCS8 keys to Istio PKI."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:60
msgid ""
"**Istio RBAC** Istio RBAC provides access control for services in Istio "
"mesh. `Learn more </docs/concepts/security/#authorization>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:64
msgid "Other"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:66
msgid ""
"**Release-Mode Binaries**. We switched release and installation default "
"to release for improved performance and security."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:69
msgid ""
"**Component Logging**. Istio components now offer a rich set of command-"
"line options to control local logging, including common support for log "
"rotation."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:73
msgid ""
"**Consistent Version Reporting**. Istio components now offer a consistent"
" command-line interface to report their version information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/news/releases/0.x/announcing-0.5/index.rst:77
msgid ""
"**Optional Instance Fields**. Within configuration, definitions of Mixer "
"instances no longer need to include every field of the associated "
"template. Omitted fields get a zero or empty value."
msgstr ""

